APARTMENT WILL BE FULLY FURNISHED. AVAILABLE FROM 07/01/2018 TO 09/30/2018! Come see this very rare and one of a kind duplex loft in a beautiful brownstone. The loft features soaring 24 ft. ceilings, a wood burning fireplace and a private terrace. Situated in a historic townhouse, this unique residence has a huge living room with six oversized windows, a large sky light, exposed brick and prewar cast-iron trelliswork. There is a half bath on the living room floor and an eat-in windowed kitchen with Gaggenau Range, double ovens, dishwasher and lots of storage. A floating wide planked staircase leads into the large sleeping loft with 8 ft. ceilings. There is also a private terrace with outdoor furniture, water and electric for entertaining and gardening, and centrally heat and air complete this amazing apartment. The townhouse is conveniently located on 25th street and 3rd Avenue close to transportation, shopping, parks, restaurants and much more. Please call or email for a private showing today. This rare loft will not last long!

column2: Sweeping Views of Central Park, Lincoln Center, Columbus Circle, and the Hudson River
Magnificent Award-Winning Penthouse Residents' Club with Pool – The Oasis
Dramatic Contemporary Lobby, featuring a Dale Chihuly Chandelier

Live on top of the world. A rare opportunity to live in this glamorous home plus a membership to the exquisite Oasis Club. Furnished or Unfurnished. Luxury at its very best with Sweeping Hudson River Views! Brilliant sun filled rooms. Live in a truly stunning Upper West Side 2 Bedroom 2.5 Bathroom home. Designer renovated with exceptional finishes and top-of-the-line details. Impeccably furnished, sleek and contemporary. Featuring gorgeous hardwood floors, state of the art appliances, custom window storage cabinetry enclosed a/c units, dramatic panoramic river and Central Park views. Extra large master bedroom offers an en suite bathroom with soaking tub and beautiful fixtures. The Living room is open with a large separate area for an office or dining. The building has recently undergone an extensive modern renovation including an exquisite Chihuly art sculpture in the 3-story lobby. In addition to white glove service, concierge and doorman, you can drive up your driveway in elegant style and be ushered in the building. The property boasts an award winning rooftop Oasis Club including spectacular views of the whole city, state of the art fitness club, swimming pool, and a gorgeous club room with an incredible outdoor terrace where you can dine and relax. This is truly a wonderful home in the most sophisticated of luxury. A half block to Central Park, close to the Lincoln Center and the grand shopping at Time Warner and Columbus Circle.

Midtown East Convertible Two Bedroom Apartment for Rent with Iconic City Views -  Near Grand Central and United Nations - Many Others Available - Call for Showings
Corner Apartment with Double High Loft Like Ceilings w/ Oversized Windows, Triple Exposure of South, West & North, Breath Taking City Views. Plus Private Storage Unit!!!

This Newly Renovated Large One Bedroom Sun Drenched Condo can be converted to a Two Bedroom and is conveniently located by Murray Hill/ Midtown East Neighborhood.  Beautiful views of  New York City which include the the Chrysler Building are easily viewable from living room, kitchen and bedroom.  This large apartment has hardwood floors and plenty of natural light.

The open kitchen has plenty of space to cook,  with stain steel appliances, full size oven,granite counter tops and Dishwasher it can host a large dinner partly if needed.  The bathroom was recently upgraded, covered in marvelous marbled and new fixtures. When it comes to closet space and extra storage no need to look any further, the apartment has more than three large closets and its own private storage unit that is the size of a small bedroom(separate floor private access).

Turtle Bay Towers is a full-service building, with live-in super, 24 hour doorman, roof deck, laundry on premises Set on a serene stretch of Midtown East just down the block from the United Nations Headquarters, Turtle Bay Towers is a full-service luxury building set in a historic prewar property. Built in 1929 as an NYC design school and known for its striking terraced façade, the 27-story tower was briefly home to a print factory. In 1979, its careful conversion to 338 luxury apartments was noted with the First Honor Award from the American Institute of Architects. The apartments here feature 12- to 14-foot ceilings, with some offering wide-open views of the Midtown skyline and the East River.

On-site amenities at this pet-friendly property include a large renovated lobby with two sitting areas, a rooftop terrace, laundry, storage, bike room, and a parking garage, plus 24-hour doorman service and a live-in super. As a condop, Turtle Bay Towers combines all the attraction of a graceful prewar property with the flexibility of a condo: no formal board approval, an open sublet policy and pied-a-terres allowed.

With a venerable history dating back to New Amsterdam, Turtle Bay is the most tranquil corner of Midtown Manhattan, known for its quiet tree-lined streets and beautiful green spaces. United Nations Plaza is just down the street, while Grand Central Station is a few blocks in the other direction and all the appeal of living in the heart of Manhattan is moments away.
Please contact Howard or Eyal for immediate showing

Harry Zikos of Nest Seekers International has been retained on an exclusive basis to represent 3 levels of commercial space available for lease at the landmarked Bogardus Building located at 75 Murray Street in TriBeCa, nestled on the north side of the block between West Broadway & Greenwich Street. The 25 foot wide cast-iron elevator building sits seconds from both Chambers Street 1,2,3, A & C train stations, in the C6-2A district, which is a commercial district outside the Central Business District. The building was built and designed by world renowned, James Bogardus in 1857 for the glassware manufacturing business of Francis & John Hopkins.

The main-ground level space, formerly occupied by Trinity Grace Church, invites you into a historic 19th century time capsule, greeted by double arch French doors and exposed brick in the lobby. The grandeur of the main level’s width and 14 foot ceilings is superimposed by the massive skylight that looks onto a courtyard. The ground and lower level have 600 amps of electrical service.

The lower level, formerly a caviar bar, preceded by a speak-easy jazz bar, is accessible by the elevator and boasts 11 foot ceilings. There is also a small kitchen area and large baths. The lower level also shares a generous and open floorplan which allows a wealth of use cases for numerous entity types.

The second level has 200 amps of electrical service and enjoys elevator access, 12 foot high ceilings, wide planked wood floors, exposed brick and renovated bathrooms. The signature of historic TriBeCa is illustrated by the openness of the space with southern exposure on from the original landmarked cast iron façade windows.

The neighborhood offers tremendous potential to organizations who need to be close to their clients, highly accessible private and public transportation hubs, vendors and booming demographics.  Some neighboring attractions, institutions and AAA tenants include Whole Foods, Equinox, Goldman Sachs New York headquarters, Bed Bath & Beyond, Stuyvesant High School, 1 World Trade Center, Fulton Center, New York Stock Exchange, Deutsche Bank, Verizon corporate offices, Brooklyn Bridge, City Hall, Borough of Manhattan Community College, numerous art galleries, TD Bank, Capital One Bank, Bank of America, Chipotle, Le Pain Quotidien and countless more!
Total Space Available: Approximately 7125 SQ FT (3 Combined Levels)
Asking price disclosed upon request. Landlord will consider all use types and leasing each space separately.
Contact Harry Zikos for more information and for a private showing of this rare historical commercial lease opportunity. Showings done by appointment only.

Chelsea is a neighborhood on the West Side of the borough of Manhattan in New York City. The district's boundaries are roughly 14th Street to the south, 30th Street to the north, the western boundary of the Ladies' Mile Historic District which lies between the Avenue of the Americas (Sixth Avenue) and Seventh Avenue to the east, and the Hudson River and West Street to the west. To the north of Chelsea is the neighborhood of Hell's Kitchen, also known as ""Clinton,"" to the northeast is the Garment District, to the east are NoMad and the Flatiron District, to the southwest is the Meatpacking District and to the southeast is the West Village. Chelsea is divided between Manhattan Community Board 4 and Manhattan Community Board 5. It contains the Chelsea Historic District and its extension, which were designated by the New York City Landmarks Preservation Commission in 1970 and 1981, respectively, and added to the National Register of Historic Places in 1977, expanded in 1982 to include contiguous blocks containing particularly significant examples of period architecture. The neighborhood is primarily residential, with a mix of tenements, apartment blocks, city housing project

Introducing THIRTEEN EAST + WEST at 436 and 442 East 13th Street, the first residential building in New York City designed by world-renowned architectural firm Tabanlioğlu Architects, providing invigorating luxury loft living in the East Village. These rare state-of-the-art new construction buildings are located within the heart of the already booming neighborhood of downtown New York City.

A sun-drenched, full-floor home at the captivating new development THIRTEEN EAST + WEST in the East Village, this 2 bedroom with windowed den, and 2.5 bathroom loft blends a host of sophisticated finishes with a functional layout that smartly uses every inch of its 1,706 SF of space. The north side of the home contains a thoughtfully placed powder room and a massive, open-concept living room/dining room/kitchen with high sound rated floor-to-ceiling windows. The kitchen—crafted with the thought of entertaining guests—features Alta Italia walnut kitchen cabinetry, Calacatta Bluette natural stone countertop and backsplash, a Blanco dual compartment sink, a Grohe gooseneck fauet and wall-mounted pot filler, and full Miele appliance package, including under-the-counter wine fridge. The south side of the residence consists of a secluded windowed home office and a pair of roomy, sun-filled south facing bedrooms faced with gorgeous Lualdi Italian doors. The master bedroom is fitted with a spacious Rosetto Italia closet and a luxurious, five-piece ensuite that boasts Montana Grey Marble floor with Volacas White polished walls and floors, a custom solid undermount tub with Montana Grey stone cladding, a Duravit toilet, Italian Newform Libera fittings & fixtures, and a quartzite sink and double vanity, and a rain shower with LED lights with 3 control system, 6-body jet and handheld system. The second bedroom comes with its own closet space and sits adjacent to the apartment’s second full bathroom. Finishing the home is a vented washer and dryer.

Composed of two, six-story buildings with facades of chic metal panels and Accoya wood cladding, THIRTEEN EAST + WEST will offer 12 sun-drenched, full-floor two-bedroom homes, with floor-to-ceiling windows, private storage, balconies, and roof decks. Each building will feature one state-of-the-art penthouse with private roof deck and a private, single car parking garage.

Amenities in each building will include private storage rooms, a virtual doorman with smartphone capability, common rooftop, and a large key-accessed elevator. Located at 436 and 442 East 13th Street, THIRTEEN EAST + WEST is half a block from the L train on 14th Street and just one block from the new Target and Trader Joes.

BRAND NEW to market is a newly renovated queen-sized 1-bedroom with great closets, big living room and warm finishes on the 2nd Floor of a doorman co-op building.  Facing a quiet, tree-lined street in West Village, the apartment is located steps from the Hudson River waterfront, amid absolutely delicious and friendly local restaurants and meeting places, and a short walk to NYC Subway, PATH trains, and CitiBike docks.   Available for August 1st move-in (see application scheduling and terms below).

A proper one-bedroom apartment with ensuite bath, the apartment features an entrance hallway, double-wide coat closet, sizeable alcove kitchen with marble countertop and stainless steel appliances, including below-counter dishwasher and full-size sink and refrigerator.   Plenty of counter space to cook on the 4-burner gas stove.   Living room is big enough for both a seating/TV area and dining table with 4 chairs.   The queen-sized bedroom has a view of leafy Washington Street, very nice-sized closet, and ceiling fan.   The newly renovated ensuite bath features brand new tile & bathtub, shower and modern vanity sink.    Air conditioning is provided by a through-the-wall unit, and building provides both heat and hot water.

A beloved whitewashed brick mid-rise building in the West Village, 165 Christopher Street  has a doorman, package room, elevators, a live-in super, porters, and a sizeable garden for use by the residents.   There also is a very big and clean laundry room in building.   As residents are all vetted, the feeling  is a warm and welcoming community of neighbors rather than that of a rental building.

Full co-op board package, Managing Agent review, and Board interview are required.    Board package is comprised of full financial disclosure, supporting documents (statements, W-2s), credit check, and three (3) personal and financial references).    Application, credit check, and management fees total $ 725 + refundable move-in and move-out deposits.   We will only select one (1) person to put forward an application.     Applicant should have very good credit, stable employment and residential history, and make an annual income of at least $ 138,000.
Application and Board Process:   Assuming a complete application with no issues, will take no more than fifteen (15) days.
One Month Security + 1st Month rent due on signing.   Tenant to set up own electric/cable/internet utilities.

860921,"545 West 20th Street, New York, NY 10011 USA",545 W 20th St,"545 W 20th St, New York, NY 10011, USA",8.0,545 West 20th Street,545,West 20th Street,1.0,43.0,10011.0,231.0,2B,42372.0,0,0,0,0,2,1,1,1,,1,Design Focused Chelsea Loft at The Lifesaver Building,lifesaver-lofts-4-br-loft-chelsea-manhattan-ny,"<div>

A palatial floor-through condo graced with a comprehensive collection of details and finishes, this 4-bedroom, 3.5-bathroom loft is a paragon of design. Features of this 4,017 sq. ft. home include gorgeous wide plank hardwood floors, huge casement windows with northern, southern, and eastern exposure, airy 11-ft ceilings, beautiful gallery-like walls, cast-iron columns, keyed elevator access, an integrated Sonos sound system, Lutron lighting, a convenient laundry and mud room, and a unique look-through gas fireplace.

The home opens directly into an expansive, 38-ft wide great room saturated with southern light. The room is anchored by an open fireplace that subtly partitions the space without closing it off, and it is served by a discreetly placed yet fully outfitted wet bar. Next to the great room sits an open-concept dining room and kitchen. Conceived by Henrybuilt, the kitchen is equipped with a massive eat-in island, custom walnut cabinetry, Carrara Gold marble countertops and backsplash, and a suite of fully-integrated stainless steel appliances from Miele. Behind the kitchen lies an additional living/media room, from which the three main bedrooms are accessed.

The spacious master suite boasts a cavernous walk-in closet, a supplementary reach-in closet, and a windowed en-suite bathroom with radiant heated floors, limestone tiles, his-and-hers sinks, a walk-in shower, and a free-standing soaking tub. Bedrooms two and three each have private closets—one has a walk-in—as well as sublime, windowed en-suite bathrooms. The fourth bedroom, which can also be used as an office, has a north-facing window and easy access to an immaculate powder room.

Taking its name from those ring shaped mints that used to be made in the building, Lifesaver Lofts is a prewar condominium nestled in the high-end neighborhood of Chelsea. The building, which is served by a part-time doorman, is across the street from the Hudson River Greenway and is less than a block away from the High Line. It sits amidst a cluster of trendy galleries, restaurants, cafes, shops and bars, and is just a short walk from Chelsea Market and the Meatpacking District. Bicycle and private storage available. This stunning duplex apartment with spectacular panoramic views is dramatically perched on the 31st and 32nd floors of the white glove glass luxury tower 860 United Nations Plaza.
The main floor to this luxurious apartment features a fabulous entertaining space with a spectacular open and airy 27 x 21 foot living room.

From its entire glass wall of windows with unencumbered panoramic views, you can feast your eyes on the river and sky and bask in the sunlight during the day or luxuriate under the romantic city lights at night next to your working fireplace. As an open canvas, the living room can be customized in a modern and loft like aesthetic or with a more traditional vision.

The living room is framed on the right by a large formal dining room with the same spectacular views and a china closet, and is framed on the left by a library or den/media room with an ensuite marble bathroom that can easily convert into a guest suite or bedroom.

The sun-flooded eat-in kitchen includes a service pantry. A laundry room with washer/dryer is situated off the kitchen next to a service entrance to the apartment and a back stairway up to the second floor bedrooms. The main floor also includes a powder room and several large closets.

Off the living room and foyer is a glamourous and gracious carpeted and glass staircase with a stainless steel handrail that leads you to the second floor where there are four bedrooms, each of which have ensuite marble bathrooms.

With dazzling uninterrupted views of the East River and sky, an oversized regal master suite with panoramic windows awaits with a walk in closet, two additional closets, and a marble bathroom with a separate shower and bathtub. Also, on the second floor, there are three additional bedrooms, all with spectacular views, and with ensuite full marble bathrooms and spacious storage closets.
The apartment has its own elevator and is furnished with window shades throughout.

The prestigious and luxurious 860 United Nations Plaza was built in 1966 by the respected architects Harrison & Abramovitz, who served as the lead architects for the United Nations Headquarters complex and for other iconic buildings including The Time-Life Building at Rockefeller Center, and designed the master plan for the Lincoln Center for the Performing Arts. The UN Plaza is a full white glove coop with a fully-equipped gym, spacious sundecks with 360 degree views of the City, striking double height lobby, concierge and doormen and other numerous staff available 24 hours, a library, garage, a private full-block driveway, a newly built entertainment/party room, golf, table tennis and billiards room, storage bin that transfers with the apartment, laundry room in the basement, and access to the basement car park from within the building.
Note: $2,157.53 group utilities and $67.20 window washing fees are due monthly in addition to the monthly maintenance. 3% flip tax is paid by the purchaser.

Every inch of this 8,300 sq. ft. home and the additional 1,130 sq. ft. of outdoor space has been thoughtfully planned with an eye towards functionality and style.

Features include floor-to-ceiling windows in every room, elevator access to all 7 stories including the roof, a chic floating staircase, engineered wide plank white oak floors, multi-zone heating and cooling, a laundry room with granite counters and an Asko washer/dryer, a one-of-a-kind in ground pool, and a quartet of private outdoor spaces.

The home begins with an airy entryway space on the garden floor and from there flows past an immaculate powder room and a private den into the stunning open-concept eat-in kitchen. Welcome to 101 Wall By the Water, the newest luxury condominium development where the Seaport meets Wall Street.  An immaculate FiDi condominium graced with a collection of stunning fixtures and finishes, this 1-bedroom, 1-bathroom home strikes the perfect balance between aesthetics and functionality. Features of this 706 sq. ft. apartment include large casement windows, northern exposure, gray herringbone hardwood floors, recessed lighting, beamed 9-ft ceilings, 11-inch baseboards, and a convenient in-unit Bosch washer and dryer.

Beyond a practical entryway space adorned with a coat closet, the home flows into an open-concept living room, dining room, and kitchen. The elegant all-white kitchen is equipped with a peninsula, custom oak cabinetry, honed marble countertops and backsplashes, and a suite of fully-integrated appliances from Bosch. The spacious master bedroom possesses a huge walk-in closet and direct access to a pristine full bathroom with marble walls and floors, chic fixtures, and a rain showerhead.

101 Wall By the Water, is a luxury condominium situated in the Financial District. The building lies just one block from the East River and provides residents with a host of thoughtful amenities that include private storage, a lounge, a quiet library, children’s playroom, game room, a fitness studio with state-of-the-art cardio and strength-training equipment, a sauna, golf simulator, and a landscaped rooftop terrace complete with a gas grill and comfortable outdoor seating. The building is surrounded by a number of high-end restaurants, cafes, bars, and shops. Nearby subway lines include the 1/2/3/4/5/N/R/W/J/Z.

At 20’ wide and over 8,000 square feet of living space, 57 West 88th Street offers the quintessential Upper West Side single family experience. Located on a classic Central Park block, the home showcases ceiling heights of up to 12’, five massive bedrooms each with en-suite bath, six full baths and four half baths spread out over seven floors! A newly installed elevator stops on each of the seven floors in the home.

Enter through garden level into a family/entertaining room leading straight through to the modern kitchen with top of the line appliances and an informal dining area. Your kitchen is laced with gorgeous Caesar stone throughout with custom made cabinets and appliances from Wolf and Miele. A walk-in pantry closet compliments the kitchen perfectly. Pass through the kitchen and experience and fabulous back garden with plenty of space for entertaining or lounging. One of your four half baths are located on this level.

A double stair case from the garden level leads to a massive parlor level. The floor is perfect for entertaining with 12’ ceilings, a generous sized formal dining room and oversized sitting/entertaining room. Two gas burning fireplaces set the tone for this level which also includes a wet bar for convenience.

The master suite encases the entire third floor of this home. An extra-large south facing bedroom exposes you to amazing southern light. Have your walk-in closet custom designed to suit your needs. The master bath located on this level is approximately 400 square feet of spa-like finishes: a double sized shower with rain head fixtures and steam option to go along with an extra-large soaking tub offer the ultimate relaxation.

Floors four and five each offer two bedrooms each with their own baths. The second of your three outdoor spaces is located on the bedroom level. In addition, a second laundry room for convenience is located on the fourth floor.

The penthouse level overs over 800 square feet of outdoor space split between front and back terraces. An excellent space for entertaining guests during the warmer months, the outdoor space has gas and water connections for convenience.

The basement level has been dugout to create a generous ceiling height. Your basement is home to a temperature controlled wine room, the larger of your two laundry rooms, a fitness area and a full bath which includes a steam shower.
57 West 88th offers the best of modern design on a classic Upper West Side block. An excellent home for anyone looking to enjoy everything that the Upper West Side has to offer.

Welcome to 101 Wall By the Water, the newest luxury condominium development where the Seaport meets Wall Street.  Nestled in the Financial District just one block from the East River, 101 Wall By the Water  is a 27-story luxury condominium that redefines contemporary elegance and design. This prewar building contains 52 units conceived by renowned designer, Piet Boon, and each one embodies his doctrine of striking the perfect balance between aesthetics and functionality.

The homes, offered in an assortment of gorgeous 1- to 4-bedroom layouts, boast a collection of stunning fixtures and finishes and many have direct views of the East River. Features include large casement windows, gray herringbone hardwood floors, beamed 9-ft ceilings, 11-inch baseboards, in-unit Bosch washers and dryers, and pristine all-white kitchens with custom oak cabinetry, honed marble countertops and backsplashes, and a suite of fully-integrated appliances by Bosch.

101 Wall By the Water provides residents with a host of thoughtful amenities. These include private storage closets, a spacious lounge complete with a bar and catering kitchen, a quiet library, children’s playroom, game room, a fitness studio with state-of-the-art cardio and strength-training equipment, sauna and steam rooms, and a golf simulator. There is also a landscaped rooftop terrace with commanding views of lower Manhattan and the East River which is furnished with a gas grill and comfortable outdoor seating. The building is close to the East River Esplanade and the newly reinvented South Street Seaport, and is surrounded by a number of high-end restaurants, cafes, bars, and shops. Nearby subway lines include the 1/2/3/4/5/N/R/W/J/Z.

An opportunity like this doesn't come along often. Enjoy this rarely available corner, spacious, 1767sqf/164sqm, two bedroom two bath, sun-drenched residence at legendary Apthorp Luxury Condominium. This unit features gorgeous original details like dark-stained herringbone floors, ornate wood moldings and elegant chandeliers. A formal entry foyer leads into exceptionally bright corner living room with classic views to the North and East. An original Apthorp mantel and decorative plaster moldings on the walls and ceiling of the living room add to the Old World grandeur. Additional features include 11' high ceilings, washer/dryer, large windowed-eat-in kitchen and ample closet space. Central AC and climate control are also all provided in each room. The Apthorp was built in 1908 by William Waldorf  Astor(converted to condo in 2008) and is one of Manhattan's most coveted and famous building in the heart of the Upper West Side. The building features 24 hour gate attendants, doormen, handymen, on site garage, 6,500 sqf fitness center with sauna, children's playroom, bicycle storage, and the famed beautifully landscaped courtyard garden and driveway. This convenient location is near both Central Park & Riverside Park, multiple subway & bus lines, grocery stores, some of the excellent restaurants and retail on the UWS.
Available for September, but negotiable for earlier move-in. This rental requires usual Condo board approval, which may take up to 2-3 weeks for processing.

The remainder of the lower level is occupied by a massive master suite. The suite contains a cavernous walk-through closet/dressing area, a separate reach-in closet, a pair of towering windows, and a large en-suite bathroom with wood-look tile floors and walls, a dual-vanity sink, a deep soaking tub, and a walk-in shower. The second level of the home contains a bedroom with two large closets, an office/study that can easily be converted into another bedroom, an enormous storage closet, and immaculate full bathroom. Both the bedroom and the office/study are open to the level below. The apartment is equipped with electronic blinds through the Living Room, Master Bedroom and Guest Bedroom. Built in the 1920s, The Printing House is a highly sought-after luxury condominium in the West Village with a sophisticated Italian Renaissance facade and full-service amenities. They include a full-time doorman, concierge services from Abigail Michaels, private landscaped mews that stretch the length of a city block, complimentary one-year memberships to the Childrens Museum of the Arts and Biscuits and Bath, access to the flagship Printing House Equinox Club, an on-site laundry facility, and on-site valet service. The building is close a number of trendy restaurants, cafes, bars, and shops, and is only a few blocks away from the Hudson River Greenway. Nearby subway lines include the A/C/E/B/D/F/M/1.

Beyond a practical entryway space adorned with a coat closet and a full bathroom, the home flows into an open-concept living room, dining room, and kitchen. The elegant all-white kitchen is equipped with a peninsula, custom oak cabinetry, honed marble countertops and backsplashes, and a suite of fully-integrated appliances by Bosch.

Both bedrooms enjoy a comfortable level of privacy thanks to a thoughtful split-wing layout. The spacious master bedroom possesses a walk-in closet as well as a pristine en-suite bathroom with dual sinks, marble walls and floors, chic fixtures, a walk-in rain shower, and a separate soaking tub. The second bedroom boasts a reach-in closet.

101 Wall By the Water is a luxury condominium situated in the Financial District. The building lies just one block from the East River and provides residents with a host of thoughtful amenities that include private storage, a lounge, a quiet library, a children’s playroom, game room, fitness studio with state-of-the-art cardio and strength-training equipment, sauna, a golf simulator, and a landscaped rooftop terrace complete with a gas grill and comfortable outdoor seating. The building is surrounded by a number of high-end restaurants, cafes, bars, and shops. Nearby subway lines include the 1/2/3/4/5/N/R/W/J/Z.
-Sponsor will pay the difference between advertised tax amount and the actual taxes due for the 18/19 tax year.

New to market is a rarely available G-line condo unit with a spectacular view in the luxurious, highly-coveted, full-service Madison Green Condominium.

Unit 18G is a west-facing, generously-sized one bedroom with plenty of room for living, dining and entertaining; complete with abundance of closets and storage space. The building itself offers wonderful amenities; including the appropriately named lounge—The Madison Club Room—on the 30th floor (Opened 24hrs), full-service doorman/concierge, garden, state-of-the-art fitness center, a parking garage, laundry room on every floor, common storage, and a bike room. Another thoughtful detail inside the building is the ATM machine in lobby. This is a great full-service condo building in the ever-so-popular Flatiron District!

Madison Green sits at the foot of Madison Square Park at the intersection of Broadway and 23rd St., surrounded by the awe-inspiring architecture of the Flatiron, Metropolitan and New York Life Insurance buildings. Even more, its advantageous location places a bevy of New York City's best restaurants and boutiques within walking distance. The location offers convenient access to transportation with the NRQ subway line just outside the door; as well as other east and west side trains just a few blocks away.

A charmingly designed co-op nestled one block away from Central Park. This updated 1-bedroom, 1-and-a-half bathroom home features gorgeous hardwood floors, large windows, a recently renovated kitchen, a spacious entry foyer, a north-west facing balcony and mutli-zone air conditioning,

Entering into the apartment through the gracious entry foyer, the apartment opens gently into the homes living room with ample storage, built in console and book cases, the space transitions seamlessly towards the outdoor balcony and adjancent kitchen. The recently renovated open kitchen is finished with granite countertops, stainless steel range, refridgerator and microwave, custom wooden cabinets, a dishwasher and center island with a breakfast bar and wine refridgerator.
The tranquil bedroom cosnsists of 2 closets and en-suite bathroom with soaking tub. Across the hall is a cozy annex to the buildings service entrance and adjoining half bathroom.

40 East 80th Street is a 26-story full service cooperative building located just off of Madison Avenue in the Upper East side, one block from Central Park. The building houses 41 apartments with semi-private landings on each floor. This polished building features a full-time doorman, live-in-super, central laundry, private storage, and bike room. The building permits guarantors, pied-a-terres, and co-purchasing. Large pets are allowed with board approval. Washer/Dryers are permitted.

Graced with top-end finishes and scintillating views of Central Park and the city skyline, this stunning 5-bedroom, 4.5-bathroom corner condo is a testament to contemporary Manhattan luxury. Features of this 3,818 sq. ft. condo include airy 10-ft ceilings, floor-to-ceiling windows, gorgeous hardwood floors, a collection of chic light fixtures, motorized shades, security cameras, two in-home washer/dryer units, two entrances, and an integrated Crestron home automation system.

Beyond a spacious entryway gallery adorned with a pair of coat closets and a powder room, the home flows into an expansive, open-concept living room, dining room, and kitchen. The space is saturated with northern and eastern light and hovers over the city skyline and the treetops of Central Park. The kitchen is equipped with a massive eat-in island, brand new stone countertops, sleek cabinetry, and a suite of high-end stainless steel appliances from Wolf, Sub-Zero, and Miele. Just off the living room lies a cozy library/den complete with an integrated speaker system.

The luminous master bedroom is a sanctuary unto itself. It features a quartet of reach-in closets, a huge walk-in closet, and an immaculate en-suite with his-and-hers sinks, a private toilet stall, a walk-in steam shower, and a deep soaking tub. The second bedroom sits adjacent to the master and boasts a trio of closets and a private en-suite bathroom. The remaining three bedrooms sit on the opposite side of the home, just off a quiet study with custom built-ins. Each bedroom has private closet space and easy access to a pristine full bathroom. All bedrooms possess blackout shades to ensure a restful night’s sleep.

The Park Millennium is a luxury condominium situated between Broadway and Columbus Avenue in Lincoln Square. The building offers residents a host of first-class amenities that include a 24-hour doorman, a concierge, a live-in super, private storage, and special membership to an enormous Equinox facility. The building is less than two blocks from Central Park, and is surrounded by upscale restaurants, bars, cafes, and shops. Lincoln Center and Columbus Circle are close by, and nearby subway lines include the 1/A/C/B/D

A sun filled penthouse condo nestled within the prestigious Brownstone Lane II, this stunning 3-bedroom, 2-bathroom home is a paradigm of modern city luxury. Features of this 1,365 sq. ft. apartment include gorgeous cherry wood floors, northern, western, and southern exposure, airy 9.5 ft. ceilings, an in-home laundry room with a washer/dryer, and a pair of private balconies.

Past an open entryway adorned with a spacious coat closet, the home flows into a bright living and dining area. The space receives northern and western bright light and leads out onto an 11-ft long north-facing balcony. Just off the dining area lies a large windowed kitchen thats been equipped with sleek granite countertops, an abundance of cabinet space, and a suite of high-end stainless steel appliances.

The master bedroom possesses its own south-facing balcony, a roomy closet, and a sumptuous en-suite bathroom with dual vanity sinks and a Jacuzzi bathtub. The second bedroom features a walk-in closet and exposure to the west and south, while the third bedroom has its own private closet as well as a large south-facing windows. Both the second and third bedrooms share easy access to a pristine full bathroom.

Located in the highly sought after South Harlem neighborhood, Brownstone Lane II is a full service condominium that offers residents a 24-hour doorman, a live-in super, a private gym, a fully landscaped and furnished courtyard, a private outdoor playground, and a playroom. With additional fees, residents also have access to individual storage units, bicycle storage, and a huge parking garage with direct elevator access. The building is a half-block away from all the trendy restaurants, bars, cafes, grocery stores, and shops that line Frederick Douglass Blvd, and is just a short walk from both Central Park and Morningside Park. Nearby subway lines include the 2/3/A/B/C/D(Only 10 Minutes to Midtown on Express Trains) Pets are welcome!

**SALES GALLERY/MODEL RESIDENCE LOCATED AT 442 EAST 13TH STREET**

Introducing THIRTEEN EAST + WEST at 436 and 442 East 13th Street, the first residential building in New York City designed by world-renowned architectural firm Tabanlioğlu Architects, providing invigorating luxury loft living in the East Village. These rare state-of-the-art new construction buildings are located within the heart of the already booming neighborhood of downtown New York City.

A sun-drenched, full-floor home at the captivating new development THIRTEEN EAST + WEST in the East Village, this 2 bedroom with windowed den, and 2.5 bathroom loft blends a host of sophisticated finishes with a functional layout that smartly uses every inch of its 1,706 SF of space. Features include an in-residence vented washer and dryer, a south-facing balcony, and access to a private, north-facing 515 square foot roof deck.

The north side of the home contains a thoughtfully placed powder room and a massive, open-concept living room/dining room/kitchen with high sound rated floor-to-ceiling windows. The kitchen—crafted with the thought of entertaining guests—features Alta Italia walnut kitchen cabinetry, Calacatta Bluette natural stone countertop and backsplash, a Blanco dual compartment sink, a Grohe gooseneck fauet and wall-mounted pot filler, and full Miele appliance package, including under-the-counter wine fridge. The south side of the residence consists of a secluded windowed home office and a pair of roomy, sun-filled south facing bedrooms faced with gorgeous Lualdi Italian doors. The master bedroom is fitted with a spacious Rosetto Italia closet and a luxurious, five-piece ensuite that boasts Montana Grey Marble floor with Volacas White polished walls and floors, a custom solid undermount tub with Montana Grey stone cladding, a Duravit toilet, Italian Newform Libera fittings & fixtures, and a quartzite sink and double vanity, and a rain shower with LED lights with 3 control system, 6-body jet and handheld system. The second bedroom comes with its own closet space and sits adjacent to the apartment’s second full bathroom. Both bedrooms open onto a private, south-facing balcony. Finishing the home is a vented washer and dryer.

Composed of two, six-story buildings with facades of chic metal panels and Accoya wood cladding, THIRTEEN EAST + WEST will offer 12 sun-drenched, full-floor two-bedroom homes, with floor-to-ceiling windows, private storage, balconies, and roof decks. Each building will feature one state-of-the-art penthouse with private roof deck and a private, single car parking garage.

Amenities in each building will include private storage rooms, a virtual doorman with smartphone capability, common rooftop, and a large key-accessed elevator. Located at 436 and 442 East 13th Street, THIRTEEN EAST + WEST is half a block from the L train on 14th Street and just one block from the new Target and Trader Joes.

Beyond a roomy entryway and a foyer/alcove which is easily transformed into a home office/third bedroom, the home flows into a luminous, open-concept living room, dining room, and kitchen. The kitchen is equipped with an eat-in peninsula, soft touch close cabinetry, granite countertops, and a suite of high-end stainless steel appliances. Both bedrooms lie on the opposite side of the home. Residence 14C is a 1,263 SF 2 bedroom / 2 bath nestled in a re-imagined Art-Deco gem situated just one block from the East River. This one-bedroom + study residence features eastern exposure on to Front Street and a flexible layout. Living spaces exude a tone of subtle luxury, greeting you with bespoke entry and interior doors with inset panels, new oversized casement windows, wide-plank herringbone floors, 11 inch baseboards, and 9 foot 6 inch plus beamed ceilings.
The chef kitchen features finely crafted white oak wood finished cabinetry, honed marble countertops, and full suite of Bosch appliances with custom millwork paneling.
Bathrooms offer marble surfaces, Kohler brushed nickel fixtures, and custom white lacquer vanities with honed marble countertops and backlit medicine cabinets.
The master bath offers separate deep soaking tub and glass-enclosed showers.
Private storage and BOSCH washer and dryer and a wine cooler are included .
Interiors, lobby, and robust amenities package including rooftop terrace, training studio, resident lounge, and kids playroom are designed by visionary Dutch architect Piet Boon.

A brand new duplex boasting private outdoor space and gorgeous finishes, this 4-bedroom, 4.5-bathroom condo is a study in contemporary city luxury. Features of this 4,098 sq. ft. floor-through apartment include whitewashed hardwood floors, huge casement windows with northern, southern, and western exposure and views of the Empire State Building and 1 WTC, chic light fixtures, an in-home washer/dryer, central heating/cooling, and a massive south-facing terrace.

The lower level of the home begins with a luminous, open-concept living room, dining room, and kitchen. All three spaces lead out onto the terrace for a seamless indoor/outdoor experience. The kitchen is equipped with sleek white countertops, a huge eat-in island, elegant cabinetry, and a suite of fully-integrated stainless steel appliances. A pair of bedrooms and an immaculate powder room finish the lower level. One of the bedrooms has a reach-in closet with a private en-suite, and the other has a walk-in closet and a windowed en-suite with dual vanity sinks and a separate shower and tub.

The upper level of the home is accessed via a set of floating stairs with modern glass railing. It contains a spacious media/family room, a third bedroom with a private closet and en-suite, and a tranquil master suite. The master suite boasts a pair of walk-in closets—one of them windowed—and a spa-like en-suite bathroom with dual vanity sinks, a glass-enclosed walk-in rain shower, and a charming claw-foot tub.

55 West 17th is a luxury condominium situated in the Flatiron District. Amenities include a fitness center, a children’s play room, bicycle storage, a fully equipped lounge, a screening room, and a landscaped terrace furnished with a grilling station and outdoor seating. The building is a short walk to both Madison Square, Gramercy, and Union Square Parks, and is surrounded by a number of restaurants, bars, cafes, and shops. It is close to more than a half-dozen major subway lines. Pets are welcome.

The discerning chef will appreciate the impeccable kitchen adorned with custom stained eucalyptus cabinetry, soft white glass cabinets with champagne bronze frames, Madre Perola quartzite stone countertops and backsplashes, a Supai limestone tiled floor, Dornbracht Platinum matte fixtures, and a butler's pantry with wet bar. The stellar Miele appliance package includes 2 integrated 30 refrigerators, a 5-burner gas range and hood, stainless steel convection and speed ovens, integrated dishwasher and 102-bottle wine fridge.

Four spacious bedrooms are highlighted by the indulgent master suite with a large dressing room and elegant spa bath, plus quiet home office on the second level. The fabulous lower/cellar level is a retreat unto itself with 1,448 sq ft of amenity space complete with a large recreation room, lounge and state-of-the-art media room. A proper laundry room is equipped with an LG Steamwasher and Ultra-Large dryer.

Introducing The Monaco, the newest Midtown East luxury condominium development. Be the first to live in residence 3B, a beautifully crafted and impeccably designed 1 bedroom + Home Office, 1.5 bathroom home with private outdoor space. With a thoughtful layout and unparalleled finishes, The Monaco is redefining Sutton Place.

Through the grand entry foyer, you are welcomed by an abundance of light through the southern facing floor-to-ceiling, tilt-n-turn Kolbe windows. The open-concept living room and state of the art chef’s kitchen is perfect for entertaining friends or for a quiet evening with family. The kitchen boasts an eat-in peninsula, custom Opal Quartz countertops with glass tile backsplash, wood cabinets with under-cabinet lighting, soft-close cabinetry and a suite of stainless steel deluxe appliances that include a Fisher & Paykel refrigerator and GE Profile range with vented hood, dishwasher and microwave. Take a step outside onto the homes private balcony that enjoys access from both the living room and master bedroom. The balcony is finished with blue stone pavers, LED lighting above and is perfect for enjoying a morning cup of coffee, glass of wine after work or to appreciate a moment of solitude overlooking the quaint and luscious gardens below.

The master bedroom is currently configured with a gracious walk-in closet that leads to the master bathroom. However, the residence benefits from the possibility of converting the oversized closet into a home office or second bedroom and still allows for each bedroom to have a closet and access to the master bath. The master bathroom features Bianco Carrera marble, Kholer fixtures, a deep soaking tub, Toto toilet and oversized vanity. The half bathroom enjoys a custom marble flooring and a laundry closet with a vented GE washer and dryer. The residence features beautiful 4-inch wide white oak engineered hardwood floors, radiant heated flooring in the bathrooms, LED down-lighting, and nearly 9-ft tall coffered ceilings throughout.

With only two units per floor, enjoy the luxury of a boutique living with the convenience and amenities of a full-service building. The Monaco is a new, one-of-a-kind luxury condominium nestled within the heart of Midtown East developed by Michael Paul Enterprises, a veteran luxury developer on the UES and Midtown East, and the experienced eyes of C3D Architecture. The new jewel of Sutton Place, the building sparkles with its limestone façade, lobby adorned with marble flooring, Venetian plaster walls, and recessed down-lighting. Amenities will include a part-time doorman, 24-hour virtual doorman, a common roof deck, a fully-equipped gym/bike room, and dedicated storage space for each homeowner. The Monaco is surrounded by the best restaurants, schools, fitness facilities, grocery stores and transportation that Midtown East has to offer!

Financial District Apartments For Sale
99 John Deco LOFTS Condominium
is a unique collection of lofts
enveloped in a building designed by the same architects as the

Empire State Building 

http://99johndecolofts.com/
This spacious LOFT has 11 foot ceilings and an expansive layout.  These
features enable a flexible comfortable utilization of space; thus allowing a
separation of the living area from the bedroom.  The kitchen is adorned
with Electrolux stainless steel appliances.  The deep gray Caesar
Stone counter tops compliment the white lacquer cabinets that feature
state-of-the-art soft closed drawers.  The bathroom is finished with <b>Calcutta
Marble tiled floors, counter tops, and back splash, offering a chic, clean
back drop.  There is ample closet space half outfitted with rods and
shelving so organization is never an issue.  Lastly, but most important, the beautiful South-facing terrace allows for a breath of fresh air and days of basking in the sun.
You come home to comfort, when you come home to John
Deco!!
99 John Street Availabilities
99 John Street: About the Building
John Deco
99 John provides stylish and impressive amenity spaces for you to entertain
family and friends, enjoy some personal time or meet up with your many
interesting neighbors. Each space allows you to personalize the experience and
make it your own. The roof top dining table provides the perfect setting for a
sunset snack and the iPod docking station in the lounge lets you pick your own
tunes. The gathering spaces are all yours… whatever your mood. And let's not
forget the 24 hour concierge, parking garage, grocery, drug store and pharmacy
FiDi
Lower Manhattan …what a place to live!! Chic shopping, cultural attractions,
dining & nightlife, convenient transportation and plenty to do outdoors.
Very much a residential neighborhood, the Financial District has some of the
City’s best schools and playgrounds. Walk the streets around 99 John and you’ll
find financiers walking along-side families. And there’s shopping too- from
Hermes and Tiffany to the shops at South Street Seaport. Plus, with 5 subway
lines, 2 water taxi docks and quick access to tunnel and bridges, the
neighborhood is as convenient to leave as it is wonderful to stay.

An impeccable condo situated in one of Manhattan’s hottest neighborhoods, this gorgeous 2-bedroom, 2.5-bathroom home blends an open plan layout with a selection of warm, textured finishes. Features of this 1,490 sq. ft. home include 70 sq. ft. outdoor space, expansive floor-to-ceiling windows, high ceilings, wide-plank distressed oak flooring, an in-home Whirlpool washer/dryer, and a pair of private bedroom balconies.

Past an entry foyer and a conveniently-placed powder room the home flows into a massive open-concept living room, dining room, and kitchen. The kitchen is equipped with custom white oak cabinetry, engineered quartz countertops and backsplash, a huge eat-in island, and a suite of high-end appliances from Sub Zero, Wolf, and Miele.

The master bedroom lies just off the living room and boasts a pair of spacious closets and a five-piece en-suite with a gray limestone double trough sink, gray limestone floors, White Persian honed marble walls, a walk-in glass-enclosed shower, and a separate soaking tub. The second bedrooms sits on the opposite side of the living room and has a pair of large closets and a full en-suite bathroom. Both bedrooms come with charming north-facing balconies.

225 West 17th is an exclusive collection of 14 apartments that exemplifies modern luxury through a lens of elegance and sophistication. The building is located in Chelsea, one of the city’s most culturally rich neighborhoods and one that is home to some of the city's most sought-after real estate. Chelsea is bounded by 14th Street to the south and 34th Street to the north, and stretches east to west from 6th Avenue to the Hudson River. It has easy access to the West Village, the Meatpacking District, and Hell’s Kitchen, and is marked by stunning art-deco architecture, exquisite dining, boutique shopping, and an abundance of recreation and park space.

Boasting sophisticated finishes and gorgeous city views, this impeccable 3-bedroom/Convertible 4, 4.5-bathoom duplex apartment is a modern expression of urban luxury. Features of the home include beautiful NEW wide plank walnut floors, motorized drapes and shades, a spacious laundry room, a fireplace, and a trio of private terraces with commanding views of the surrounding skyline. There is also an in-wall speaker system throughout the home.

The upper level of the home contains three of the home’s four bedrooms as well as a bright, open-concept living room, dining room, and kitchen. The dining room features a pair of bars and a contemporary gas fireplace while the living room opens onto wrap-around terrace that faces north and east. The custom kitchen, designed by Downsview, is equipped with Calacatta marble countertops and backsplash, an eat-in island, a pantry, a farmhouse sink, and a suite of high-end stainless steel appliances including a Sub-Zero refrigerator and a Wolf range. Each of the bedrooms on the upper level contain immaculate ensuite bathrooms. Two of the three bedrooms have private closet space while the third has its own wrap-around terrace that faces north and west.

The master suite occupies the entirety of the lower level. It consists of a large sitting room, a dressing room, an abundance of closet space, a wrap-around terrace, and a spa-like master bathroom with marble walls and floors, a custom chandelier, a walk-in steam shower, dual-vanity sinks, and a separate soaking tub.

Trump Plaza is a 39-story building in the Upper East Side. Amenities include 24-hour doorman, a luxurious lobby, a concierge, a fitness center, a playroom, a private community garden, a garage, and storage space. Pets and pieds-a-terre are allowed. It is surrounded by a number of restaurants, cafes, shops, and grocery stores. Nearby subway lines include the 4, 5, 6, N, Q, R, and W. 2% flip tax paid by Buyer.

Move in ASAP! When walking into this stunning lofted duplex, you will be taken aback by the 20-foot, double high windows that complement the spacious, airy living/dining room and open kitchen. The apartment is also environmentally concious with features like responsibly harvested, 10” wide, white oak plank floors and energy efficient UV blocking glass to maintain a comfortable temperature throughout.

The custom kitchen is outfitted with painted Baltic birch kitchen cabinetry by Descience, it is FSC certified, and thoughtfully planned with a large pantry, featuring an appliance garage and integrated recycling bins.  The kitchen employs elegant minimalism with white corian countertops and backsplash, including integral sink, Vola fixtures by Arne Jacobsen, and appliances by Sub Zero and Miele. The functionality of the kitchen is heightened with an Insinkerator garbage disposal, a water filtration system, and an under counter wine cooler.

The full-size staircase leads up to the bedroom, which enjoys the same floor-to-ceiling window exposure as the downstairs living room. The bedroom features expansive Poliform closets that were carefully customized for this apartment.  The master bath is replete with Calacatta gold marble, a steam shower, and Vola fixtures.
This apartment includes a Miele washer and dryer.  There is also bike storage available in the basement. Building amenities include 24hr doorman, architecturally designed common garden.

721 3rd Avenue is ideally situated on the northeast corner of 3rd Avenue and 45th Street in Midtown East on 3rd Avenue which acts as the gateway that connects Midtown East by northern traffic flow to the Upper East Side, Long Island and Long Island City/Queens via Midtown Tunnel and Queensboro Bridge, FDR Highway and downtown Manhattan.

As one of the most important commercial office centers in New York City with over 70 million square feet of office space, it serves as the center point that is equidistant to its densely business and commercial counterpart in Midtown, the residential alcoves of Sutton Place and Turtle Bay and the headquarters of the United Nations.

Residents within a 5-block radius in all directions include, to name a few, the world-renowned Chrysler Building, MetLife Building, United Nations Headquarters, JP Morgan Chase Headquarters, Grand Central Terminal, W New York Hotel, Hilton Hotels and Turtle Bay and Sutton Place residential areas. In proximity within the past two years, there has been 6+ new commercial and residential high-rise developments as well as an area rezoning that will allow for new construction of approximately 6.5 million square feet of office space.
721 3rd Avenue has a convenience and walking score of 9.2/10 as it benefits from both easy access to and from its location.

Within walking distance lies Grand Central Terminal which has the most railroad platforms in the entire world, the 4/5/6/7 subway lines that connect Midtown East to Midtown West, downtown and Queens, and the Financial District to the Upper East Side. In addition, the E/M subway lines connect Midtown East to Midtown West with additional services to the Financial District throughout the entire West Side and center of Manhattan as both subway lines travel downtown and to Brooklyn.

Nestled in serene Hudson Heights, the Townhomes on Cabrini offer a one of a kind, enviable opportunity to live in a collection of three stunning brand new, 22 foot wide, townhomes situated in picturesque Northern Manhattan. Modeled in traditional style with the allure of a reminiscent era of New York, which has long been forgotten, and infused with the finest of sleek modern day amenities, the Townhomes on Cabrini offer a quite respite from the hustle and bustle of New York, set against the green scape and Hudson River backdrop that only Hudson Heights can offer.  Each townhouse harmoniously blends the stone façade, with large casement windows, nine to ten foot ceilings with a well thought out gracious floorplan and high end finishes and fixtures as well as subtle design details that provide for a truly comfortable and enjoyable lifestyle.

The 17th Century inspired stone façade combined with the striking contrast of the dark solid mahogany doors greets visitors to a charm of historic grandeur as they enter the luxuriousness of the well-appointed interior. The entry foyer, featuring a beautiful limestone floor, leads to a spacious first floor containing a generous rec room.A marvelous open floor plan layout consisting of the living room, dining room and kitchen awaits on the second floor. Integrating an elegant mix of dark and light materials, the kitchen utilizes use of light cabinetry, double honed white marble countertops, and a dark island. In addition, top of the line stainless steel appliances are among the high quality features that will aid in the comfort of cooking. Custom millwork and wide plank dark hardwood floors are found throughout along with a dark wood paneled ceiling in the living room which provides for an allure perfect for entertaining guests. The dining room leads out to a graciously manicured lush backyard via use of double wide doors. Three large bedrooms and two bathrooms along with a laundry room are allocated to the third floor adding to the functionality of the layout. The capacious master suite and a junior master bedroom are both situated on the fourth floor. White washed, wide plank hardwood floors are found throughout all of the bedrooms. The master suite features a splendid master bathroom with dual vanities and a standalone deep soaking tub, a large walk-in closet and a private balcony overlooking the backyard. Modern day amenities found throughout the home are radiant heating, smart home automation, recessed energy efficient LED lighting, and an in-home elevator. The east facing back façade utilizes floor to ceiling glass panels which allow for sunlight to fill and warm the home throughout the day. The landscaped roof deck, accessible via the elevator, offers spectacular views of the Hudson River as well as the skyscrapers situated to the south, and contains a lounge area with a fire pit ideal for spending time with family and friends.

The surrounding neighborhood of Hudson Heights offers a resplendent feel, the likes of which are not seen anywhere else in Manhattan. Located between West 181st St and Fort Tryon Park, it provides ease of access to downtown via the express A train within 25 minutes. Situated along the Hudson River, west of Broadway, stunning vistas of the river, George Washington Bridge and the Jersey palisades are enjoyed from certain vantage points, specifically Bennett Park, which at 265 feet above sea level is the highest natural peak in all of Manhattan. The neighborhood is mostly comprised of pre-war buildings built in Art Deco and Tudor Revival styles mirroring the Upper West Side. Neighboring Fort Tryon Park provides the opportunity to relax outdoors as it contains 67 acres, full of winding paths, perfect for enjoying strolls and breathtaking views. The Cloisters in Fort Tryon Park is a museum well known for housing and displaying art from the Metropolitan Museum of Art. Recently, the neighborhood has enjoyed a renaissance as new businesses such as 181 Cabrini, a popular café and wine bar, along with Bangkok Heights which offers a wide array of Thai food, and Saggio, a Sicilian restaurant and beer garden have taken residency along West 181st Street. Hudson Heights also allows quick commute via automobile as it is situated along a major thorough fare route connecting the George Washington Bridge with several major highways including the Henry Hudson Parkway, Harlem River Drive, Major Deegan Expressway, as well as I-95, along with Route 4 and the Palisades Interstate Parkway in New Jersey. As such, Hudson Heights offers a fantastic alternative to lower Manhattan.

Chelsea is a neighborhood on the West Side of the borough of Manhattan in New York City. The district's boundaries are roughly 14th Street to the south, 30th Street to the north, the western boundary of the Ladies' Mile Historic District which lies between the Avenue of the Americas (Sixth Avenue) and Seventh Avenue to the east, and the Hudson River and West Street to the west. To the north of Chelsea is the neighborhood of Hell's Kitchen, also known as ""Clinton,"" to the northeast is the Garment District, to the east are NoMad and the Flatiron District, to the southwest is the Meatpacking District and to the southeast is the West Village. Chelsea is divided between Manhattan Community Board 4 and Manhattan Community Board 5. It contains the Chelsea Historic District and its extension, which were designated by the New York City Landmarks Preservation Commission in 1970 and 1981, respectively, and added to the National Register of Historic Places in 1977, expanded in 1982 to include contiguous blocks containing particularly significant examples of period architecture. The neighborhood is primarily residential, with a mix of tenements, apartment blocks, city housing project.

A pristine corner co-op suffused with natural light, this renovated 1-bedroom, 1-bathroom home is the quintessence of classic New York City living. Features of this 888 sq. ft. home include beautiful hardwood floors, northern and western exposure, sleek light fixtures, and through-wall HVAC units.

Past an open entryway adorned with a pair of large coat closets, the home flows into an expansive living and dining area. A huge north-facing window anchors the living space, while the dining area leads into a semi-open windowed kitchen equipped with chic granite countertops, a mosaic tile backsplash, elegant cabinetry, and a suite of stainless steel Bosch appliances. The large bedroom features double exposure, ample closet space, and easy access to a windowed full bathroom.

Situated in Lenox Hill, 440 East 62nd is a 19-story full-service co-op with a classic redbrick façade. The building has a full-time doorman, a live-in super, a rooftop deck with stunning views, and a convenient 24-hour laundry room. It is close to a number of restaurants, shops, bars, and cafes, and is only a few blocks away from the N/R/W/F/Q/4/5/6 subway lines. Pets and pied-à-terre allowed.

A sun filled penthouse condo nestled within the prestigious Brownstone Lane II, this stunning 3-bedroom, 2-bathroom home is a paradigm of modern city luxury. Features of this 1,365 sq. ft. apartment include gorgeous cherry wood floors, northern, western, and southern exposure, airy 9.5 ft. ceilings, an in-home laundry room with a washer/dryer, a pair of private balconies, and INCREDIBLY LOW MONTHLIES due to a 25-year tax abatement that runs through 2032.

Past an open entryway adorned with a spacious coat closet, the home flows into a bright living and dining area. The space receives northern and western bright light and leads out onto an 11-ft long north-facing balcony. Just off the dining area lies a large windowed kitchen that’s been equipped with sleek granite countertops, an abundance of cabinet space, and a suite of high-end stainless steel appliances.

The master bedroom possesses its own south-facing balcony, a roomy closet, and a sumptuous en-suite bathroom with dual vanity sinks and a Jacuzzi bathtub. The second bedroom features a walk-in closet and exposure to the west and south, while the third bedroom has its own private closet as well as a large south-facing windows. Both the second and third bedrooms share easy access to a pristine full bathroom.

Located in the highly sought after South Harlem neighborhood, Brownstone Lane II is a full service condominium that offers residents a 24-hour doorman, a live-in super, a private gym, a fully landscaped and furnished courtyard, a private outdoor playground, and a playroom. With additional fees, residents also have access to individual storage units, bicycle storage, and a huge parking garage with direct elevator access. The building is a half-block away from all the trendy restaurants, bars, cafes, grocery stores, and shops that line Frederick Douglass Blvd, and is just a short walk from both Central Park and Morningside Park. column2: Located in the heart of Long Island City, this  can converted 2 bed 2 bathroom apartment with a living room/den with has protected views of Manhattan. A southwestern exposed 1100 SF open layout including an additional private 1100 SF wrap around terrace. Besides the views of midtown, the terrace comes fully furnished with including 6 seat teak dining table, teak flooring, and a zen garden waterfall and Japanese maple, bamboo, lavender plantings. Originally a 2 bedroom, this apartment has the flexibility to be converted back to a 2 bedroom easily by installing a wall. Its current layout features an over-sized open kitchen, custom cabinets, stainless steel appliances. Caesar-stone counter tops, and a Bosch dishwasher. Right off the kitchen you will enjoy a separate dining room that overlooks the Empire State Building. The living room/den boasts a south facing picture window and a full bathroom. The Master bedroom has his & her customized closets by Transform, an en-suite double sink bathroom and a private entrance onto the terrace. The over-sized laundry room has custom storage and an in unit washer/dryer. Other customizations include custom closets in foyer, laundry room, and automated shades on all windows.

The building is full-service and features a 24-hour doorman, gym, kids room, landscaped roof-deck and a garden courtyard. This home is 3 blocks away from the 7-train at Vernon/ Jackson situated conveniently one stop from Grand Central in Manhattan. Email for a viewing today. </section>

An immaculate 2 Bedroom/2 Bathroom apartment graced with amazing light, southern exposure and partial Hudson River views. This corner home is one of a kind in the building and provides great privacy and peacefulness as it lies underneath a large terrace of the apartment above. Beyond a functional entryway space adorned with a large coat closet, the residence flows into an expansive living/dining room and large windowed kitchen. The kitchen is equipped with granite countertops, Miele and Sub-Zero appliances. The master bedroom suite features a bathroom with a large window, two spacious closets and views of the city. The second bedroom or guest room/home office has custom built-ins, a built-in book shelve, two closets and can comfortably fit a queen size bed. The apartment also features:
• Custom built-ins in the living room for extra storage.
• Additional heating units in the kitchen, master bath and hallway.

The Avery Condominium is a full service building with 24-hour doorman, a concierge, fitness center, billiards room, screening room, resident lounge/library with Wifi, children's play room, conference room, courtyard and a parking garage.

State of the art modern Loft where Soho meets Tribeca.

This beautiful two bedroom, one-and-a half-bathroom residence boast 1,662sf of open-concept living space, which was meticulously designed and renovated by the original owner. Its spaciousness is amplified by soaring ceilings, which features the original wood beams, oversized north and east facing windows that are accented by exposed brick walls and hardwood floors throughout—this is the epitome of New York City living.

Upon entering, you are greeted by a large 20x19 light-filled living room which flows seamlessly into the dining area and open kitchen—a great entertaining space. The large chef-style kitchen—designed and created by an almost century old Italian designer, Molteni—features a center island with honed Carrara marble countertops, contemporary cabinetry, and is complimented by German-engineered stainless steel Gaggenau Hausgeräte appliances.

497 Greenwich street is a beautifully designed glass structure interwoven with the original brick façade, designed by Dutch architect Winka Dubbeldam, and is situated on a gorgeous tree-lined street it Hudson Square. However, just steps away around the corner is the bustling intersection of SoHo, TriBeCa, and the West Village. Residents and their guests get to enjoy the great amenities and services this building has to offer, including a theater, state-of-the-art fitness center (which includes a swimming pool and two saunas), wine cellar, garden, 24-hour doorman and concierge, and a duplex guest suite.

An impeccable duplex nestled within the exclusive SoHo Mews, this 3-bedroom, 2.5-bathroom (easily converted to a full bath) home blends the convenience of a luxury condo with the tranquility of a private townhouse. Features of this 2,877 sq. ft. residence include wide plank Mafi Volcano hardwood floors, airy 10'2-ft ceilings, electronic shades, a Nest thermostat system, security cameras, home automation from Savant, an in-home washer/dryer, a home office, and a charming 280 sq. ft. garden terrace.

Just off a spacious entry gallery adorned with a coat closet lies large media room/third bedroom, which has its own closet and eastern exposure. From there, the home flows past an immaculate powder room and into an expansive, open-concept living room, dining room, and kitchen. The living and dining area lead out to the garden, while the Gwathmey Siegel-designed kitchen features a massive eat-in island, Jet Mist granite countertops, custom elm cabinetry, a cavernous pantry, and a suite of high-end stainless steel appliances from Dacor and Liehberr.

The upper level of the home contains an office space as well as a pair of large bedrooms that overlook the garden. The master bedroom boasts a trio of reach-in closets, a huge walk-in closet, and a spa-like en-suite bathroom with marble tiles, radiant heated floors, dual vanity sinks, a walk-in shower, and a separate bathtub. The second bedroom has its own closet as well as a private en-suite.

Located on a secluded street in the heart of SoHo, SoHo Mews is a full-service luxury condominium offering residents a host of first-class amenities. These include a full-time doorman, a live-in super, a state-of-the-art fitness center, an on-site parking garage, and a 4,000 sq. ft. residents-only courtyard that was designed by renowned landscape architect Peter Walker. SoHo Mews is steps away from a number of trendy restaurants, bars, cafes, and shops, and is close to the A/C/E/N/R/Q/W/1/6 subway lines.. Pets are welcome.

Nestled in serene Hudson Heights, the Townhomes on Cabrini offer a one of a kind, enviable opportunity to live in a collection of three stunning brand new, 22 foot wide, townhomes situated in picturesque Northern Manhattan. Modeled in traditional style with the allure of a reminiscent era of New York, which has long been forgotten, and infused with the finest of sleek modern day amenities, the Townhomes on Cabrini offer a quite respite from the hustle and bustle of New York, set against the green scape and Hudson River backdrop that only Hudson Heights can offer.  Each townhouse harmoniously blends the stone façade, with large casement windows, nine to ten foot ceilings with a well thought out gracious floorplan and high end finishes and fixtures as well as subtle design details that provide for a truly comfortable and enjoyable lifestyle.

The 17th Century inspired stone façade combined with the striking contrast of the dark solid mahogany doors greets visitors to a charm of historic grandeur as they enter the luxuriousness of the well-appointed interior. The entry foyer, featuring a beautiful limestone floor, leads to a spacious first floor containing a generous rec room.A marvelous open floor plan layout consisting of the living room, dining room and kitchen awaits on the second floor. Integrating an elegant mix of dark and light materials, the kitchen utilizes use of light cabinetry, double honed white marble countertops, and a dark island. In addition, top of the line stainless steel appliances are among the high quality features that will aid in the comfort of cooking. Custom millwork and wide plank dark hardwood floors are found throughout along with a dark wood paneled ceiling in the living room which provides for an allure perfect for entertaining guests. The dining room leads out to a graciously manicured lush backyard via use of double wide doors. Three large bedrooms and two bathrooms along with a laundry room are allocated to the third floor adding to the functionality of the layout. The capacious master suite and a junior master bedroom are both situated on the fourth floor. White washed, wide plank hardwood floors are found throughout all of the bedrooms. The master suite features a splendid master bathroom with dual vanities and a standalone deep soaking tub, a large walk-in closet and a private balcony overlooking the backyard. Modern day amenities found throughout the home are radiant heating, smart home automation, recessed energy efficient LED lighting, and an in-home elevator. The east facing back façade utilizes floor to ceiling glass panels which allow for sunlight to fill and warm the home throughout the day. The landscaped roof deck, accessible via the elevator, offers spectacular views of the Hudson River as well as the skyscrapers situated to the south, and contains a lounge area with a fire pit ideal for spending time with family and friends.

The surrounding neighborhood of Hudson Heights offers a resplendent feel, the likes of which are not seen anywhere else in Manhattan. Located between West 181st St and Fort Tryon Park, it provides ease of access to downtown via the express A train within 25 minutes. Situated along the Hudson River, west of Broadway, stunning vistas of the river, George Washington Bridge and the Jersey palisades are enjoyed from certain vantage points, specifically Bennett Park, which at 265 feet above sea level is the highest natural peak in all of Manhattan. The neighborhood is mostly comprised of pre-war buildings built in Art Deco and Tudor Revival styles mirroring the Upper West Side. Neighboring Fort Tryon Park provides the opportunity to relax outdoors as it contains 67 acres, full of winding paths, perfect for enjoying strolls and breathtaking views. The Cloisters in Fort Tryon Park is a museum well known for housing and displaying art from the Metropolitan Museum of Art. Recently, the neighborhood has enjoyed a renaissance as new businesses such as 181 Cabrini, a popular café and wine bar, along with Bangkok Heights which offers a wide array of Thai food, and Saggio, a Sicilian restaurant and beer garden have taken residency along West 181st Street. Hudson Heights also allows quick commute via automobile as it is situated along a major thorough fare route connecting the George Washington Bridge with several major highways including the Henry Hudson Parkway, Harlem River Drive, Major Deegan Expressway, as well as I-95, along with Route 4 and the Palisades Interstate Parkway in New Jersey. As such, Hudson Heights offers a fantastic alternative to lower Manhattan.

 Do not miss your opportunity to live in one of Manhattans most iconic buildings! This spectacular open, sun-drenched, corner unit 60A, at the Frank Gehry building. On the southern side of the 6th floor the first of the building's two terraces is outfitted with grills, cafe seating, and dining cabanas with picnic tables. On the 7th floor a 50-foot pool is set within a skylit space surrounded by a series of glass doors that retract fully, creating a seamless integration with the building's wraparound sundeck. Overlooking City Hall Park to the north, a large drawing room with multiple seating areas and a grand piano is located adjacent to a private dining room. Both are available for private events that can be served from a chef's demonstration and catering kitchen. A 3,300 square foot state-of-the-art fitness center with a view of the Brooklyn Bridge and a spa treatment suite are also located on the 7th floor. The 8th floor offers group fitness, Boxing Studio, and private training studios, a Library with a well-curated selection of books and periodicals, a Tween's Den, a Children's Playroom, and a Screening Room with Gehry-designed amphitheatre seating that can be reserved for private events. The location is unbeatable, you are steps away from the heart of Tribeca with amazing restaurants such as Bubbys, Nobu, and Locanda Verde and have easy access to Whole Foods. This gem is conveniently located across the street from the Brooklyn Bridge City Hall Subway stop and is a 5 minute walk to the Fulton Street station for the rest of your transportation needs. You do not want to miss this incredible opportunity to call the Gehry Building home!
